<subSubSection id="C325B8D6FFF2FFF8F188FF4AC765FEEC" pageId="5" pageNumber="1214" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B80EB5DFFF2FFF8F188FF4AC765FEEC" blockId="5.[178,1085,219,358]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1214">
C o m m e n t: The known distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F90DEFFF2FFF8F3BBFF4AC798FF79" authorityName="ASSING &amp; WUNDERLE" authorityYear="1995" box="[641,748,219,240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Habrocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis id="B94B374FFFF2FFF8F3BBFF4AC798FF79" box="[641,748,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1214">H. indicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which extends from the Himalaya (
<collectingCountry id="F328ABCDFFF2FFF8F1D1FF69C45FFE87" box="[235,299,248,270]" name="Nepal" pageId="5" pageNumber="1214">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, North 
<collectingCountry id="F328ABCDFFF2FFF8F042FF69C4DAFE87" box="[376,430,248,270]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="1214">India</collectingCountry>
) to the southeast of the Chinese province Yunnan, is mapped in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE96ACFFF2FFF8F188FE84C43AFEA2" author="ASSING V" box="[178,334,277,299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1214" pagination="1217 - 1227" refId="ref2806" refString="ASSING V. (2014): A revision of the Habrocerinae of the world. V. A new species of Habrocerus from China and additional records (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 46 (2): 1217 - 1227." type="journal article" year="2014">ASSING (2014)</bibRefCitation>
. The above record is based only on a female and should be considered tentative, but the recent male-based record from the environs of Pingbian in southeastern Yunnan is only some 
<quantity id="4CC746B8FFF2FFF8F0B5FEC1C4BAFEEF" box="[399,462,336,358]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="1214" unit="km" value="60.0">60 km</quantity>
away.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
